{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/staticrwlockref"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"abstract":[{"text":"The [struct","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","isActive":true},{"text":"] struct represents a read-write lock. A read-write","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"lock can be used for protecting data that some portions of code only","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"read from, while others also write. In such situations it is"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"desirable that several readers can read at once, whereas of course","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"only one writer may write at a time."}],"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockRef\/init(_:)-10mti","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockRef\/init(_:)-37bn","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockRef\/init(_:)-3nxea","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockRef\/init(_:)-56q6n","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockRef\/init(_:)-qfhc","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockRef\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockRef\/init(constPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockRef\/init(gconstpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockRef\/init(gpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockRef\/init(mutating:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockRef\/init(opaquePointer:)"],"anchor":"Initializers","title":"Initializers","generated":true},{"title":"Instance Properties","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockRef\/ptr"],"anchor":"Instance-Properties"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockRef\/PointerWrapper-Implementations","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockRef\/StaticRWLockProtocol-Implementations"],"generated":true,"title":"Default Implementations","anchor":"Default-Implementations"}],"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol"],"title":"Conforms To","type":"conformsTo","kind":"relationships"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockRef"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"StaticRWLockRef"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Take a look at the following example:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["  GStaticRWLock rwlock = G_STATIC_RW_LOCK_INIT;","  GPtrArray *array;","","  gpointer","  my_array_get (guint index)","  {","    gpointer retval = NULL;","","    if (!array)","      return NULL;","","    g_static_rw_lock_reader_lock (&rwlock);","    if (index < array->len)","      retval = g_ptr_array_index (array, index);","    g_static_rw_lock_reader_unlock (&rwlock);","","    return retval;","  }","","  void","  my_array_set (guint index, gpointer data)","  {","    g_static_rw_lock_writer_lock (&rwlock);","","    if (!array)","      array = g_ptr_array_new ();","","    if (index >= array->len)","      g_ptr_array_set_size (array, index + 1);","    g_ptr_array_index (array, index) = data;","","    g_static_rw_lock_writer_unlock (&rwlock);","  }"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":null},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This example shows an array which can be accessed by many readers"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"my_array_get()"},{"type":"text","text":" function) simultaneously, whereas the writers"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(the ","type":"text"},{"code":"my_array_set()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" function) will only be allowed once at a time"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and only if no readers currently access the array. This is because","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of the potentially dangerous resizing of the array. Using these"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"functions is fully multi-thread safe now.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Most of the time, writers should have precedence over readers. That","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"means, for this implementation, that as soon as a writer wants to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"lock the data, no other reader is allowed to lock the data, whereas,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of course, the readers that already have locked the data are allowed","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to finish their operation. As soon as the last reader unlocks the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"data, the writer will lock it."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Even though [struct"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock"},{"text":"] is not opaque, it should only be used","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"with the following functions.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_static_rw_lock_*"},{"type":"text","text":" functions can be used even if"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Thread.init"},{"text":"] has not been called. Then they do nothing, apart","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_static_rw_lock_*_trylock"},{"text":", which does nothing but returning true.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A read-write lock has a higher overhead than a mutex. For example, both"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"code":"StaticRWLock.reader_lock","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] and [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"StaticRWLock.reader_unlock"},{"type":"text","text":"] have"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to lock and unlock a [struct"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"], so it takes at least twice the time"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"to lock and unlock a [struct","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock"},{"type":"text","text":"] that it does to lock and unlock a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[struct","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","isActive":true},{"text":"]. So only data structures that are accessed by multiple","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"readers, and which keep the lock for a considerable time justify a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[struct","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"]. The above example most probably would fare better with a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[struct"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","isActive":true},{"text":"].","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockRef","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" type acts as a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying "},{"code":"GStaticRWLock","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It exposes methods that can operate on this data type through "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" conformance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockRef"},{"type":"text","text":" only as an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"text":" reference to an existing ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GStaticRWLock"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","type":"reference"},{"text":" (instead of ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockRef","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":") if you want to use Automatic Reference Counting for memory management of the underlying "},{"code":"GStaticRWLock","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}]}]}]}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"title":"StaticRWLockRef","symbolKind":"struct","role":"symbol","externalID":"s:4GLib15StaticRWLockRefV","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"StaticRWLockRef","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"StaticRWLockRef","kind":"identifier"}],"roleHeading":"Structure"},"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/StaticRWLockRef/init(_:)-3nxea":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockRef\/init(_:)-3nxea","role":"symbol","title":"init(_:)","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Conditional initialiser from an optional, no